Analyzing the impact of different video topics and different days of the week on how long people spend watching videos

Do Food Videos Change Our Viewing Time?

As shown, people who watched food videos tend to spend slightly more time watching overall, though the difference is modest.But it could show that mukbang slightly increases the length of time people watch videos.

What Are the Most Engaging Topics?

We look at the most interesting video topics that students reported. This scatterplot shows how long people spent on different topics.

Some topics like travel, games, and cooking appear frequently. Even within the same genre, people’s engagement can vary widely.

Is the length of time people watch videos affected by the day of the week?

This plot shows the total amount of watch time grouped by day of the week. It helps us understand if there is a pattern across the week.

We can see that some weekdays like Friday and Saturday have higher total watch times, while Monday is the lowest — possibly due to workload or routines. It seems that people are more inclined to watch longer videos on Friday when they finish work, and may not like to watch videos on Monday when they start work due to work or school reasons
